      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>Is <i>tert</i>-butoxide anion a strong enough base to react significantly with water? In other words, can a solution of potassium <i>tert</i>-butoxide be prepared in water? The p<i>K</i><sub>a</sub> of <i>tert</i>-butyl alcohol is approximately 18.</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBb1VRIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--60429e1bf4c0a6ffdabed7da6227b2ee7e93d900/OChem_02_EC_017.jpg\" alt=\"The structure of potassium tertiary-butoxide.\">",
